History was made during the U.S. elections when Sarah E McBride became the country's first trans state senator – and, briefly, the highest-ranking trans official in the country. "I ran to make a difference in my community," she said after her win.

In his first week in office, President Biden overturned the controversial ban on trans people newly joining the U.S. military. "This is such a huge relief," said Nic Talbott, who was forced to drop out of the Army Reserve Officers' Training Corps.

Bangladesh gained its first trans news anchor amidst hopes of greater acceptance in the socially conservative country. "This could be revolutionary," said Tashnuva Anan, who now regularly appears on Bangladeshi television.
